               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Makātib-i Aḥmad Ghazālī va ʻAyn al-Quz̤āt by Ghazzālī, Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad, -1126</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008112367" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1127-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Letters, described in a later hand on the title page as Makātib-i Aḥmad Ghazālī va 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659043.0x000001 viaf_96998098">ʻAyn al-Quz̤āt, of Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad</persName>Ghazzālī and his pupil 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_96998098" role="aut">ʻAyn al-Quz̤āt Hamadānī</persName>. A more complete copy is Add.16823 (Rieu p. 411). This copy contains only about a fifth of the total text.
                        </p>
                        <p>68 ff.; 25 lines per page; old naskhi; rubications; lacunae; somewhat worm-eaten and water-stained; 13th century.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657499.0x000001 viaf_42230786">Ghazzālī, Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad, -1126</persName>
